[
  {
    "id": 1,
    "text": "<para er-custom-ele=\"true\" ele-id=\"254E136C\" store=\"635\" er_para_index_id=\"fe-1772171652046118-124\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" data-alignment=\"left-justified\" data-indent-type=\"first-line\" data-left-indent=\"25pt\" data-right-indent=\"0pt\" data-special-indent=\"-19.5pt\" data-space-above=\"0pt\" data-space-below=\"0pt\" style=\"margin: calc(10px) 0px 0pt 25px; padding-left: 25px; text-indent: -19.5px;\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">The economic implications of this shift have been debated extensively; see E. P. Thompson, \n\t<i ele-id=\"ds-55A4FDA8\" store=\"641\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Customs in Common</i> (New York: New Press, \n\t<span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774615713949486\"></span>\n\t<link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000700\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-AA1B023D\" store=\"642\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">1991</link1>), pp. 12–15; Patrick O’Brien, \n\t<i ele-id=\"ds-8D046698\" store=\"643\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">The Industrial Revolution</i> (Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, \n\t<span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774615713949150\"></span>\n\t<link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000701\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-D104322A\" store=\"644\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">2004</link1>). These works provide contrasting interpretations.\n</para>",
  },
  {
    "id": 2,
    "text": "<para er-custom-ele=\"true\" ele-id=\"254E136C\" store=\"635\" er_para_index_id=\"fe-1772171652046118-124\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" data-alignment=\"left-justified\" data-indent-type=\"first-line\" data-left-indent=\"25pt\" data-right-indent=\"0pt\" data-special-indent=\"-19.5pt\" data-space-above=\"0pt\" data-space-below=\"0pt\" style=\"margin: calc(10px) 0px 0pt 25px; padding-left: 25px; text-indent: -19.5px;\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">This topic has been widely discussed in recent scholarship. See John Brewer, <i ele-id=\"ds-C814AB4C\" store=\"636\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">The Sinews of Power</i> (London: Routledge, <span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774615713949816\"></span><link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000501\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-C8F97226\" store=\"638\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">1989</link1>), p. 45, for further details.</para>"
  },
  {
    "id": 3,
    "text": "<para er-custom-ele=\"true\" ele-id=\"254E136C\" store=\"635\" er_para_index_id=\"fe-1772171652046118-124\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" data-alignment=\"left-justified\" data-indent-type=\"first-line\" data-left-indent=\"25pt\" data-right-indent=\"0pt\" data-special-indent=\"-19.5pt\" data-space-above=\"0pt\" data-space-below=\"0pt\" style=\"margin: calc(10px) 0px 0pt 25px; padding-left: 25px; text-indent: -19.5px;\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Peter Clark, <i ele-id=\"ds-D2145D7A\" store=\"637\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">English Provincial Society</i> (Oxford: <span class=\"ins cts-0\" data-cid=\"261\" data-userid=\"39753\" data-username=\"Copy editor US\" data-time=\"1772569657598\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"1772570652283947\" ele-id=\"fe-1772570698497320\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Oxford University Press</span>, <span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774615713949816\"></span><link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000600\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-C8F97226\" store=\"638\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">1977</link1>); Paul Slack, <i ele-id=\"ds-81447748\" store=\"639\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Poverty and Policy in Tudor and Stuart England</i> (London: Longman, <span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774615713949504\"></span><link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000601\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-27906B99\" store=\"640\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">1988</link1>).</para>",
  },
  {
    "id": 4,
    "text": "<para er-custom-ele=\"true\" ele-id=\"254E136C\" store=\"635\" er_para_index_id=\"fe-1772171652046118-124\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" data-alignment=\"left-justified\" data-indent-type=\"first-line\" data-left-indent=\"25pt\" data-right-indent=\"0pt\" data-special-indent=\"-19.5pt\" data-space-above=\"0pt\" data-space-below=\"0pt\" style=\"margin: calc(10px) 0px 0pt 25px; padding-left: 25px; text-indent: -19.5px;\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">For a revised interpretation, see Mark Overton, <i ele-id=\"ds-9E60D873\" store=\"645\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Agricultural Revolution in England</i>, 2<span class=\"ins cts-0\" data-cid=\"120\" data-userid=\"39753\" data-username=\"Copy editor US\" data-time=\"1772569118732\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"177257065228333\" ele-id=\"fe-1772570698497269\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">nd</span><span class=\"del cts-0\" data-cid=\"121\" data-userid=\"39753\" data-username=\"Copy editor US\" data-time=\"1772569119225\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"1772570652283178\" ele-id=\"fe-1772570698497100\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">, </span>edn (Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, <span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774615713949875\"></span><link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000800\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-F9DB00DC\" store=\"646\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">1996</link1>).</para>",
  },
  {
    "id": 5,
    "text": "<para er-custom-ele=\"true\" ele-id=\"254E136C\" store=\"635\" er_para_index_id=\"fe-1772171652046118-124\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" data-alignment=\"left-justified\" data-indent-type=\"first-line\" data-left-indent=\"25pt\" data-right-indent=\"0pt\" data-special-indent=\"-19.5pt\" data-space-above=\"0pt\" data-space-below=\"0pt\" style=\"margin: calc(10px) 0px 0pt 25px; padding-left: 25px; text-indent: -19.5px;\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Christopher Hill, <i ele-id=\"ds-A364C498\" store=\"629\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">The World Turned Upside Down</i> (London: Penguin, <span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774542605156617\"></span><link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000900\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-D03C895B\" store=\"630\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">1972</link1>), p. 88. See also: J. C. Davis, <i ele-id=\"ds-8A8D397D\" store=\"631\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Utopia and the Ideal Society</i> (Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, <span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774542605156723\"></span><link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000901\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-54FF1975\" store=\"632\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">1981</link1>).</para>",
  },
  {
    "id": 6,
    "text": "<para er-custom-ele=\"true\" ele-id=\"3A1B2C3D\" store=\"801\" er_para_index_id=\"fe-1772171652046118-301\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" data-alignment=\"left-justified\" data-indent-type=\"first-line\" data-left-indent=\"25pt\" data-right-indent=\"0pt\" data-special-indent=\"-19.5pt\" data-space-above=\"0pt\" data-space-below=\"0pt\" style=\"margin: calc(10px) 0px 0pt 25px; padding-left: 25px; text-indent: -19.5px;\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">It is argued that the spread of literacy in rural England fundamentally changed local governance structures; see John Smith, <i ele-id=\"ds-00112233\" store=\"802\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Education and Society in Early Modern England</i> (Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, <link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000101\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-44556677\" store=\"803\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">2003</link1>), pp. 45–60.</para>",
  },
  {
    "id": 7,
    "text": "<para er-custom-ele=\"true\" ele-id=\"3B2C3D4E\" store=\"804\" er_para_index_id=\"fe-1772171652046118-302\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" data-alignment=\"left-justified\" data-indent-type=\"first-line\" data-left-indent=\"25pt\" data-right-indent=\"0pt\" data-special-indent=\"-19.5pt\" data-space-above=\"0pt\" data-space-below=\"0pt\" style=\"margin: calc(10px) 0px 0pt 25px; padding-left: 25px; text-indent: -19.5px;\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Recent studies highlight the impact of mechanized farming on smallholders in the 18th century; see Laura Brown, <i ele-id=\"ds-11223344\" store=\"805\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Agricultural Innovation and Rural Society</i> (Oxford: Oxford University Press, <link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000102\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-55667788\" store=\"806\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">2010</link1>), pp. 120–145.</para>",
  },
  {
    "id": 8,
    "text": "<para er-custom-ele=\"true\" ele-id=\"3C3D4E5F\" store=\"807\" er_para_index_id=\"fe-1772171652046118-303\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" data-alignment=\"left-justified\" data-indent-type=\"first-line\" data-left-indent=\"25pt\" data-right-indent=\"0pt\" data-special-indent=\"-19.5pt\" data-space-above=\"0pt\" data-space-below=\"0pt\" style=\"margin: calc(10px) 0px 0pt 25px; padding-left: 25px; text-indent: -19.5px;\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">It should be noted that local taxation patterns influenced village economies over centuries; see Michael Green, <i ele-id=\"ds-22334455\" store=\"808\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Fiscal Systems and Rural Life</i> (London: Routledge, <link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000103\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-66778899\" store=\"809\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">2007</link1>), pp. 33–58.</para>",
  },
  {
    "id": 9,
    "text": "<para er-custom-ele=\"true\" ele-id=\"4F6A7B8C\" store=\"900\" er_para_index_id=\"fe-1772171652046118-401\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" data-alignment=\"left-justified\" data-indent-type=\"first-line\" data-left-indent=\"25pt\" data-right-indent=\"0pt\" data-special-indent=\"-19.5pt\" data-space-above=\"0pt\" data-space-below=\"0pt\" style=\"margin: calc(10px) 0px 0pt 25px; padding-left: 25px; text-indent: -19.5px;\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">The role of guilds in regulating trade and protecting artisans has been widely discussed; see Thomas A. Green, <i ele-id=\"ds-55667788\" store=\"901\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Guilds and Urban Economies in Early Modern England</i> (London: Routledge, <link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000201\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-66778899\" store=\"902\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">2008</link1>), pp. 34–56. It is also argued that guilds served as centers of social cohesion and mutual aid, particularly during periods of economic instability; see Elizabeth Harper, <i ele-id=\"ds-77889900\" store=\"903\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Artisan Communities and Social Networks</i> (Oxford: Oxford University Press, <link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000202\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-88990011\" store=\"904\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">2011</link1>), pp. 78–101. Moreover, archival evidence indicates that the enforcement of apprenticeship rules directly impacted urban labor mobility; see Mark L. Johnson, <i ele-id=\"ds-99001122\" store=\"905\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Labor and Regulation in Tudor Towns</i> (Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, <link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000203\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-10111213\" store=\"906\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">2015</link1>), pp. 45–67. Taken together, these studies suggest that guilds were both economic and social institutions that shaped early modern urban life in multifaceted ways.</para>",
  },
  {
    "id": 10,
    "text": "<para er-custom-ele=\"true\" ele-id=\"254E136C\" store=\"635\" er_para_index_id=\"fe-1772171652046118-124\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" data-alignment=\"left-justified\" data-indent-type=\"first-line\" data-left-indent=\"25pt\" data-right-indent=\"0pt\" data-special-indent=\"-19.5pt\" data-space-above=\"0pt\" data-space-below=\"0pt\" style=\"margin: calc(10px) 0px 0pt 25px; padding-left: 25px; text-indent: -19.5px;\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Christopher Hill, <i ele-id=\"ds-A364C498\" store=\"629\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">The World Turned Upside Down</i> (London: Penguin, <span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774542605156617\"></span><link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000900\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-D03C895B\" store=\"630\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">1972</link1>), p. 88. See also: J. C. Davis, Quinzani R.T, <i ele-id=\"ds-8A8D397D\" store=\"631\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Utopia and the Ideal Society</i> (Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, <span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774542605156723\"></span><link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000901\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-54FF1975\" store=\"632\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">1981</link1>).</para>",
  }
]